    "For example, data crawled from the Internet is often stored in formats such as WARC, WAT and WET.",
    "Text from HTML pages can be converted to plain text from WET files or through alternative methods.",
    "Step 6: Encoding Detection.",
    "Employ encoding detection tools to identify the text encoding, ensuring that text is stored in the correct encoding format.",
    "Incorrect encoding may lead to garbled characters or data corruption."
